  (576, 694, 'Did he adjust well to school?', 'Doctor'),
  (577, 694, 'and my husband grabbed his arm, you know, and pulled him away from them.', 'Wendy'),
  (578, 694, 'Hey, wasn''t it around here that the Donner party got snowbound?', 'Wendy'),
  (579, 694, 'I know all about cannabilism, I saw it on T.V.', 'Danny'),
  (580, 694, 'No, my son''s discovered the games room.', 'Jack'),
  (581, 694, 'God, I''ve never seen anything like this before.', 'Wendy'),
  (582, 694, 'We''ve had four presidents who stayed here, lots of movie stars.', 'Ullman'),
  (583, 694, 'It''s quite an attraction around here.', 'Ullman'),
  (584, 694, 'That''s fine because basically the Snowcat operates very much like a car and it won''t take you long to get the hang of it.', 'Ullman'),
  (585, 694, 'I''m afraid you''re not going to do too well here unless you''ve brought your own supplies.', 'Ullman'),
  (586, 694, 'The Torrances are going to take care of the Overlook for us this winter.', 'Ullman'),
  (587, 694, 'Now are you a Winnie or a Freddie?', 'Halloran'),
  (588, 694, 'Torrance - it''s big but it still ain''t nothing but a kitchen...', 'Halloran'),
  (589, 694, 'Well what''s your favorite food then?', 'Halloran'),
  (590, 694, 'Well, it''s possible, but I honestly don''t remember calling him that since we''ve been with you.', 'Wendy'),
  (591, 694, 'sociables, finger rolls and seven kinds of what-have-you.', 'Halloran'),
  (592, 694, 'You folks don''t mind if I give Danny some ice cream, while we''re waiting for you?', 'Halloran'),
  (593, 694, 'You know what I''m talking about, don''t you?', 'Halloran'),
  (594, 694, 'Is Tony the one that tells you things?', 'Halloran'),
  (595, 694, 'Maybe he showed me something.', 'Danny'),
  (596, 694, 'Well, you know Doc, when something happens it can leave a trace of itself behind...', 'Halloran'),
  (597, 694, 'You''re scared of Room 237, ain''tcha?', 'Danny'),
  (598, 694, 'How about taking me for a walk after you''ve finished your breakfast?', 'Wendy'),
  (599, 694, 'When I came up here from my interview, it was as though I had been here before.', 'Jack'),
  (600, 694, 'Let''s take the rest of this walking, huh?', 'Wendy');
INSERT INTO quotes (id, movie_id, text, character) VALUES
  (601, 694, 'Yet to our north, to our west, it is snowing and cold, and it''s moving', 'Man Announcer'),
  (602, 694, 'Whenever you come in here and interrupt me, you''re breaking my concentration.', 'Jack'),
  (603, 694, 'This is KDK 12 calling KDK 1.', 'Wendy'),
  (604, 694, 'Most winters they stay that way until spring.', 'Ranger'),
  (605, 694, 'It''s just like pictures in a book, Danny.', 'Tony'),
  (606, 694, 'Not right now, Daddy''s asleep.', 'Wendy'),
  (607, 694, 'Are you having a good time?', 'Jack'),
  (608, 694, 'You know that, don''t you, huh?', 'Jack'),
  (609, 694, 'Here let''s get up off the floor.', 'Wendy'),
  (610, 694, 'God, I''d give anything for a drink?', 'Jack'),
  (611, 694, 'You''re not to busy, are you?', 'Jack'),
  (612, 694, 'How are things going, Mr.', 'Lloyd'),
  (613, 694, 'I love the little son-of-a- bitch.', 'Jack'),
  (614, 694, 'All I tried to do was to pull him up.', 'Jack'),
  (615, 694, 'He went up into one of the bedrooms, the door was open, and he saw this crazy woman in the bath-tub.', 'Wendy'),
  (616, 694, 'Highways are blocked by snowdrifts.', 'Glen Rinker'),
  (617, 694, 'Our weather expert Walter Cronice will have the local forecast later on.', 'Glen Rinker'),
  (618, 694, 'I mean, maybe Danny made a mistake?', 'Wendy'),
  (619, 694, 'It wouldn''t be that different from the episode that he had before we came up here, would it?', 'Jack'),
  (620, 694, 'Wendy, I have let you fuck up my life so far, but I''m not going to let you fuck this up!', 'Jack'),
  (621, 694, 'Oh why don''t you call me back in about eh twenty minutes?', 'Ranger'),
  (622, 694, 'I''ve made an awful mess of your jacket, sir.', 'Grady'),
  (623, 694, 'Awfully nice of you to say.', 'Jack'),
  (624, 694, 'Ah ha, it''s coming off now, sir.', 'Grady'),
  (625, 694, 'chopped your wife and daughters up into little bits, and eh...', 'Jack'),
  (626, 694, 'Your son has a very great talent.', 'Grady'),
  (627, 694, 'But I corrected them, sir.', 'Grady'),
  (628, 694, 'Danny can''t wake up, Mrs.', 'Tony'),
  (629, 694, 'I''ll call you back later.', 'Halloran'),
  (630, 694, 'I''m calling from Stapleton Airport.', 'Halloran'),
  (631, 694, 'Larry, just between you and me, we''ve got a very serious problem with the people who are taking care of the place.', 'Halloran'),
  (632, 694, 'and, Charlie, we have what you call your bad day out there.', 'Voice Over Radio'),
  (633, 694, '...listen to me for a minute, will you, hon?', 'Wendy'),
  (634, 694, 'Maybe it was about Danny.', 'Jack'),
  (635, 694, 'You think maybe he should be taken to a doctor?', 'Jack'),
  (636, 694, 'Have you ever thought for a single solitary moment about my responsibilities to my employers?', 'Jack'),
  (637, 694, 'I''m not going to hurt you.', 'Jack'),
  (638, 694, 'I think you hurt my head real bad.', 'Jack'),
  (639, 694, 'No need to rub it in, Mr.', 'Jack'),
  (640, 694, 'I fear that is the only thing to do.', 'Grady'),
  (641, 19995, 'When I was lying there in the VA hospital, with a big hole blown through the middle of my life, I started having these dreams of flying.', 'Voice'),
  (642, 19995, 'Let''s get it straight up front.', 'Jake'),
  (643, 19995, 'You''re ruinin'' my good mood.', 'Jake'),
  (644, 19995, 'People, you have been in cryo for five years, nine months and twenty two days.', 'Med Tech'),
  (645, 19995, 'Seen a lotta guys leave this place in a wheelchair.', 'Wainfleet'),
  (646, 19995, 'As head of security, it''s my job to keep you alive.', 'Quaritch'),
  (647, 19995, 'Me and Norm were out here to drive these remotely controlled bodies called avatars.', 'Max'),
  (648, 19995, 'Which is why they offered me this gig, because I can link with Tommy''s avatar, which was insanely expensive.', 'Jake'),
  (649, 19995, 'Who''s got my goddamn cigarette?!', 'Grace'),
  (650, 19995, 'You know -- the PhD who trained three years for this mission.', 'Grace'),
  (651, 19995, 'You know I enjoy our little talks.', 'Selfridge'),
  (652, 19995, 'But after -- how many years?', 'Selfridge'),
  (653, 19995, 'How much link time have you logged?', 'Grace'),
  (654, 19995, 'Phase-lock ninety nine percent.', 'Tech'),
  (655, 19995, 'And this clearcutting really stirs up the hornet''s nest.', 'Quaritch'),
  (656, 19995, 'This low gravity makes you soft.', 'Quaritch'),
  (657, 19995, 'They could fix this if I rotated back.', 'Quaritch'),
  (658, 19995, 'That sounds real good, Colonel.', 'Jake'),
  (659, 19995, 'That means you''re in my world, got it?', 'Grace'),
  (660, 19995, 'If they see us taking our samples, treating the forest with respect -- Not trampling everything in sight -- they may reach out to us.', 'Grace'),
  (661, 19995, 'How will they know we''re here?', 'Norm'),
  (662, 19995, 'Are you going to help with this gear?', 'Grace'),
  (663, 19995, 'I don''t have all goddamn night!', 'Jake'),
  (664, 19995, 'You are like a baby, making noise, don''t know what to do.', 'Neytiri'),
  (665, 19995, '--you just have to get to know me.', 'Jake'),
  (666, 19995, 'His alien smell fills my nose', 'Eytukan'),
  (667, 19995, 'Just ask Doctor Augustine.', 'Jake'),
  (668, 19995, 'Okay, again, a whole lot slower.', 'Jake'),
  (669, 19995, 'Yeah, Doc -- and you are not going to believe where I am.', 'Jake'),
  (670, 19995, 'I wouldn''t care except --', 'Selfridge'),
  (671, 19995, 'He''s the clan leader -- -- but she''s the spiritual leader.', 'Grace'),
  (672, 19995, 'Don''t do anything unusually stupid.', 'Grace'),
  (673, 19995, 'I''m not about to let Quaritch and Selfridge micro-manage this thing.', 'Grace'),
  (674, 19995, 'We''re in the flux vortex.', 'Grace'),
  (675, 19995, 'He falls off the frickin'' turnip truck and all of a sudden he''s cultural ambassador!?', 'Norm'),
  (676, 19995, 'Norm''s attitude has improved lately.', 'Jake'),
  (677, 19995, 'I See you, Neytiri Mo''at''ite.', 'Grace'),
  (678, 19995, 'She''s always going on about the flow of energy-- the spirits of the animals and what not --', 'Jake'),
  (679, 19995, 'You''re still losing weight.', 'Grace'),
  (680, 19995, 'And this is your check up from the neck up, Marine.', 'Grace'),
  (681, 19995, 'Right in front of Neytiri.', 'Grace'),
  (682, 19995, 'Iknimaya translates roughly as stairway to heaven.', 'Jake'),
  (683, 19995, 'But I was born to do this.', 'Jake'),
  (684, 19995, 'Something big is going on in there, biologically.', 'Grace'),
  (685, 19995, 'Your warriors -- hide inside machines -- fight from far away.', 'Tsu''Tey'),
  (686, 19995, 'I can barely remember my old life.', 'Jake'),
  (687, 19995, 'Parker, it''s their ancestral home.', 'Grace'),
  (688, 19995, 'Look, you''ve given me plenty of usable intel.', 'Quaritch'),
  (689, 19995, 'You''re just not strong enough.', 'Grace'),
  (690, 19995, 'Our life out there takes millions of dollars of machinery to sustain.', 'Grace'),
  (691, 19995, 'I''m not that guy any more.', 'Jake'),
  (692, 19995, 'Did your Spirit Animal come?', 'Eytukan'),
  (693, 19995, 'And you may choose a woman.', 'Neytiri'),
  (694, 19995, 'Where ever you are, come back to me now.', 'Neytiri'),
  (695, 19995, 'You mated with this woman?!', 'Tsu''Tey'),
  (696, 19995, 'I have Colonel Quaritch with me and --', 'Trudy'),
  (697, 19995, 'Parker, listen, there may still be time to --', 'Grace'),
  (698, 19995, 'Just tell him what you know in your heart.', 'Jake'),
  (699, 19995, 'What the hell have you people been smoking out there?', 'Selfridge'),
  (700, 19995, 'They''re never going to leave Hometree.', 'Jake'),
  (701, 19995, 'And the equipment is totalled.', 'Wainfleet'),
  (702, 19995, 'Then you''re justified in taking it.', 'Jake'),
  (703, 19995, 'Unless you want your girlfriend in there when the axe comes down, you get them to evacuate.', 'Selfridge'),
  (704, 19995, 'I fell in love-- with the forest, with the Omaticaya People -- -- with you.', 'Jake'),
  (705, 19995, 'Give me forty millimeter gas rounds, right in the front door.', 'Quaritch'),
  (706, 19995, 'That was unexpectedly satisfying.', 'Max'),
  (707, 19995, 'Good, `cause that''s where we''re going.', 'Jake'),
  (708, 19995, 'The way I had it figured, Toruk is the baddest cat in the sky.', 'Jake'),
  (709, 19995, 'Look where we are, Grace.', 'Jake'),
  (710, 19995, 'With your permission, I will Speak now.', 'Jake'),
  (711, 19995, 'When Toruk Macto called them, they came.', 'Jake'),
  (712, 19995, 'When we destroy it, we will blast a crater in their racial memory so deep they won''t come within a thousand klicks of this place.', 'Quaritch'),
  (713, 19995, 'I don''t know how secure this channel is.', 'Max'),
  (714, 19995, 'Because I gave it to him on a plate.', 'Jake'),
  (715, 19995, 'I''ve never done this in my life.', 'Jake'),
  (716, 19995, 'But I could use a little help here.', 'Jake'),
  (717, 19995, 'I hear this is worse than death for you, chief.', 'Wainfleet'),
  (718, 19995, 'Valkyrie Two is breaking off.', 'Pilot'),
  (719, 19995, 'It''s all over Quaritch --', 'Jake'),
  (720, 19995, 'Now do the duty of Olo''eyctan.', 'Tsu''Tey'),
  (721, 27205, 'But he asked for you by name.', 'Attendant'),
  (722, 27205, 'I know the tricks, and I can teach them to your subconscious so that even when you''re asleep, your guard is never down.', 'Cobb'),
  (723, 27205, 'With a clean dive, perhaps.', 'Cobb'),
  (724, 27205, 'And, judging by the decor, we''re in your mind, aren''t we, Arthur?', 'Mal'),
  (725, 27205, 'You know the corporation who hired us won''t accept failure.', 'Cobb'),
  (726, 27205, 'How could you get the carpet wrong?!', 'Arthur'),
  (727, 27205, 'Philippa, can you ask Grandma to pick up the phone-', 'Cobb'),
  (728, 27205, 'That''s not how I deal with things.', 'Cobb'),
  (729, 27205, 'Because I can find my own way to square things with Cobol.', 'Cobb'),
  (730, 27205, 'So do you want to take a leap of faith, or become an old man, filled with regret, waiting to die alone?', 'Saito'),
  (731, 27205, 'It''ll take more than the occasional stuffed animal to convince those children they still have a father.', 'Miles'),
  (732, 27205, 'No, you taught me to navigate other people''s minds.', 'Cobb'),
  (733, 27205, 'You told me it would free me.', 'Cobb'),
  (734, 27205, 'Aren''t you going to tell me anything?', 'Ariadne'),
  (735, 27205, 'So well that you don''t feel your brain doing the creating.', 'Cobb'),
  (736, 27205, 'your mind can''t create all this.', 'Ariadne'),
  (737, 27205, 'Someone had to design the dreams.', 'Cobb'),
  (738, 27205, 'That''s one way we get at a subject''s thoughts-his mind creates the people, so we can literally talk to his subconscious.', 'Cobb'),
  (739, 27205, 'They''re going to attack us?', 'Ariadne'),
  (740, 27205, 'Look, this isn''t about me-', 'Cobb'),
  (741, 27205, 'That''s not an issue for me.', 'Ariadne'),
  (742, 27205, 'Word is, you''re not welcome in these parts.', 'Eames'),
  (743, 27205, 'It''s not just about depth.', 'Eames'),
  (744, 27205, 'We''ll meet downstairs in half an hour.', 'Cobb'),
  (745, 27205, 'How big do the levels have to be?', 'Ariadne'),
  (746, 27205, 'What was she like in real life?', 'Ariadne'),
  (747, 27205, 'They''ll be able to blackmail governments, dictate policy.', 'Saito'),
  (748, 27205, 'You''re well informed, Mr.', 'Cobb'),
  (749, 27205, 'The only way to know you''ve done the job is if I go in with you.', 'Saito'),
  (750, 27205, 'I just-I need to test some things.', 'Cobb'),
  (751, 27205, 'And she''d sabotage the operation.', 'Ariadne'),
  (752, 27205, 'A dream within a dream within a dream?', 'Arthur'),
  (753, 27205, 'Forgive me for wanting a little specificity, Eames.', 'Arthur'),
  (754, 27205, 'We''ve arranged for you to spend several days...', 'Saito'),
  (755, 27205, 'I''ve had time to learn Browning''s physical presence and mannerisms...', 'Eames'),
  (756, 27205, 'Twelve hours and forty-five minutes-one of the longest flights in the world.', 'Saito'),
  (757, 27205, 'It creates a very clear connection between dreamers, whilst actually accelerating brain function.', 'Yusuf'),
  (758, 27205, 'That, Ariadne, would be a kick.', 'Eames'),
  (759, 27205, 'That we''d grow old together.', 'Cobb'),
  (760, 27205, 'Moments I turned into dreams so I could change them.', 'Cobb'),
  (761, 27205, 'How can it not matter to you where that train will take you?', 'Mal'),
  (762, 27205, 'If you don''t want it to be me then you need to show Arthur what I just saw.', 'Ariadne'),
  (763, 27205, 'Couldn''t you have peed before you went under?', 'Arthur'),
  (764, 27205, 'Why were we all ambushed, Arthur?!', 'Cobb'),
  (765, 27205, 'What do you mean, it won''t wake him?', 'Eames'),
  (766, 27205, 'Let''s just get him upstairs.', 'Arthur'),
  (767, 27205, 'So you led us into a war zone with no way out.', 'Eames'),
  (768, 27205, 'Doesn''t mean you don''t know the combination.', 'Cobb'),
  (769, 27205, 'He never gave me the combination.', 'Fischer'),
  (770, 27205, 'When we get you down to the next level, the pain will be less intense.', 'Cobb'),
  (771, 27205, 'Cobb, you might have convinced the rest of this team to carry on with the job.', 'Ariadne'),
  (772, 27205, 'The problem is knowing that it''s not real.', 'Cobb'),
  (773, 27205, 'That to get home we''d have to kill ourselves.', 'Cobb'),
  (774, 27205, 'Let''s go back inside and talk about this, please.', 'Cobb'),
  (775, 27205, 'She''d had herself declared sane by three different psychiatrists.', 'Cobb'),
  (776, 27205, 'If we''re going to succeed in this, you''re going to have to forgive yourself, and you''re going to have to confront her.', 'Ariadne'),
  (777, 27205, 'The entire empire would cease to exist.', 'Browning'),
  (778, 27205, 'Shouldn''t be afraid to dream a little bigger, Arthur-', 'Eames'),
  (779, 27205, 'How about a pretty young lady I''ve used before?', 'Eames'),
  (780, 27205, 'Because it involves telling the mark that he''s dreaming.', 'Arthur'),
  (781, 27205, 'My specialty is subconscious security.', 'Cobb'),
  (782, 27205, 'But I can explain all this.', 'Cobb'),
  (783, 27205, 'If this is a dream, I have to kill myself and wake up-', 'Fischer'),
  (784, 27205, 'they demanded the first numbers to pop into my head.', 'Fischer'),
  (785, 27205, 'Good-looking fellow, I''m sure.', 'Browning'),
  (786, 27205, 'Fischer Morrow''s been my entire life.', 'Browning'),
  (787, 27205, 'Whose subconscious are we going into?', 'Ariadne'),
  (788, 27205, 'What we''re looking for is going to be in the most heavily fortified section.', 'Cobb'),
  (789, 27205, 'They need a new route-a direct route.', 'Cobb'),
  (790, 27205, 'When the van hits the water.', 'Cobb'),
  (791, 27205, 'You''re clear, but hurry-there''s an army headed your way...', 'Cobb'),
  (792, 27205, 'Saito''s not going to last, Eames.', 'Cobb'),
  (793, 27205, 'You reconstructed them all from memory?', 'Ariadne'),
  (794, 27205, 'So certain of your world.', 'Mal'),
  (795, 27205, 'Choose your reality like I did.', 'Mal'),
  (796, 27205, 'How could you know it was a lie?', 'Mal'),
  (797, 27205, 'A truth that she had once known, but had chosen to forget...', 'Cobb'),
  (798, 27205, 'If I stay, can she take him back?', 'Cobb'),
  (799, 27205, 'But I couldn''t make you real.', 'Cobb'),
  (800, 27205, ') And I''m going to, Uncle Peter.', 'Fischer');
INSERT INTO quotes (id, movie_id, text, character) VALUES
  (801, 157336, 'I''m on hold with the INS.', 'Assistant'),
  (802, 157336, 'Because if it had we''d all be dead by now.', 'Ansen'),
  (803, 157336, 'I need to know how that thing got there.', 'Nsa Agent'),
  (804, 157336, 'The Europeans put up some of the funding...', 'Ansen'),
  (805, 157336, 'You don''t make it, my boys won''t get to see you lose.', 'Cooper'),
  (806, 157336, 'Be nice to Murph''s teacher.', 'Donald'),
  (807, 157336, 'It means what can happen will happen.', 'Cooper'),
  (808, 157336, 'It was looking for something.', 'Cooper'),
  (809, 157336, 'You have to be realistic.', 'Principal'),
  (810, 157336, 'Maybe your grandchildren will be able to attend college.', 'Principal'),
  (811, 157336, 'If we had any of them left the doctors might have been able to find the cyst in my wife''s brain before she died, rather than afterwards.', 'Cooper'),
  (812, 157336, 'Never seen one like it, though.', 'Cooper'),
  (813, 157336, 'There''s no one for it to report to.', 'Cooper'),
  (814, 157336, 'It doesn''t bother me that he can''t go.', 'Cooper'),
  (815, 157336, 'You''re staying here and cleaning the house.', 'Cooper'),
  (816, 157336, 'Tell the boy to stop hitting me.', 'Robot'),
  (817, 157336, 'Now who''s stealing from who?', 'Cooper'),
  (818, 157336, 'Most of the disk was noise.', 'Cooper'),
  (819, 157336, 'Are you using that for guidance?', 'Cooper'),
  (820, 157336, 'Same as the rest of these people.', 'Cooper'),
  (821, 157336, 'I''ve found the best way to earn a person''s trust is to trust them.', 'Case'),
  (822, 157336, 'The probe has taken a great deal longer to return to us than we hoped.', 'Case'),
  (823, 157336, 'In the last century strands were limited to one or two species.', 'Brand'),
  (824, 157336, 'You''ve known this for how long?', 'Cooper'),
  (825, 157336, 'I didn''t think I''d be around for the end of it.', 'Donald'),
  (826, 157336, 'You''re not coming back, are you?', 'Murph'),
  (827, 157336, 'So we arranged to take some off their hands.', 'Brand'),
  (828, 157336, 'I thought humans were more solitary.', 'Cooper'),
  (829, 157336, 'We''re headed for this smaller black hole.', 'Case'),
  (830, 157336, 'It''s like walking on the rim of the volcano.', 'Doyle'),
  (831, 157336, 'If I''m wrong, we''ll die, same as we''d die here anyway.', 'Brand'),
  (832, 157336, 'What makes you think we could understand their plan, either?', 'Roth'),
  (833, 157336, 'So why are you painting it?', 'Cooper'),
  (834, 157336, 'No -- I mean how is your mood?', 'Case'),
  (835, 157336, 'Your programming is better than ours.', 'Case'),
  (836, 157336, 'This conversation is making you uncomfortable.', 'Case'),
  (837, 157336, 'Black holes are a more stable supply of power than stars in many ways.', 'Brand'),
  (838, 157336, 'It could be gravitational turbulence.', 'Case'),
  (839, 157336, 'We''re being pulled by its swirl.', 'Roth'),
  (840, 157336, 'The engines don''t have enough power to push us back.', 'Case'),
  (841, 157336, 'How could they all have landed in the same place?', 'Cooper'),
  (842, 157336, 'Then how did the probe that Cooper found return?', 'Brand'),
  (843, 157336, 'Cooper, want to make yourself useful?', 'Brand'),
  (844, 157336, 'It''s not your light they''re responding to.', 'Roth'),
  (845, 157336, 'Because I''m not going anywhere.', 'Brand'),
  (846, 157336, 'But I haven''t seen anything.', 'Brand'),
  (847, 157336, 'I just -- I could have sworn it just moved.', 'Brand'),
  (848, 157336, 'Then why are they killing each other?', 'Cooper'),
  (849, 157336, 'They haven''t developed tools, culture, language.', 'Brand'),
  (850, 157336, 'People starved to death sitting on the ground, waiting for someone to come.', 'Cooper'),
  (851, 157336, 'But why didn''t they come?', 'Cooper'),
  (852, 157336, 'They built the colony and radioed home.', 'Case'),
  (853, 157336, 'It''s not going to hit the planet, but it''s going to come close.', 'Doyle'),
  (854, 157336, 'They found a way to make gravity.', 'Cooper'),
  (855, 157336, 'You''re missing the bigger picture.', 'Roth'),
  (856, 157336, 'In the morning we''re taking this and going home.', 'Case'),
  (857, 157336, 'We will provide food and shelter and await further instructions.', 'Liu'),
  (858, 157336, 'This site was deemed unacceptable.', 'Liu'),
  (859, 157336, 'The main thruster fuel supply.', 'Cooper'),
  (860, 157336, 'The knowledge of how to build it.', 'Roth'),
  (861, 157336, 'Control systems inside are online.', 'Doyle'),
  (862, 157336, 'If we account for the blue shift then the computer might find something in there.', 'Cooper'),
  (863, 157336, 'if they''re even still alive.', 'Cooper'),
  (864, 157336, 'It''ll be destroyed, like everything else.', 'Brand'),
  (865, 157336, 'We''re not going to be able to slow down.', 'Doyle'),
  (866, 157336, 'I''ve got a surprise for you, Dad.', 'Tom'),
  (867, 157336, 'And I''ve known that for a long time.', 'Tom'),
  (868, 157336, 'You really think we''re the last humans alive anywhere?', 'Cooper'),
  (869, 157336, 'I think it lives in the bulk -- the space that the wormholes traverse.', 'Brand'),
  (870, 157336, 'Time moves very slowly here 130.', 'Tars'),
  (871, 157336, 'This was their best solution.', 'Tars'),
  (872, 157336, 'They weren''t interested in the other wormholes because their mission was to return home.', 'Cooper'),
  (873, 157336, 'There would already be some evidence.', 'Brand'),
  (874, 157336, 'I have to find out what happened to my sons.', 'Cooper'),
  (875, 157336, 'But we don''t get to go with.', 'Cooper'),
  (876, 157336, 'I made some changes to the machine.', 'Emily Cooper'),
  (877, 157336, 'This is the Space Station Joseph A.', 'Doctor'),
  (878, 157336, 'But there are some questions I''ve been told to ask.', 'Administrator'),
  (879, 157336, 'But there are great numbers of candidates.', 'Administrator'),
  (880, 157336, 'You''re the oldest man in the human race.', 'Administrator'),
  (881, 438631, 'We are the secret of the Universe.', 'Reverend Mother Ramallo'),
  (882, 438631, 'The huge wind organ BLOWS louder and louder, obscuring her voice.', 'Reverend Mother Ramallo'),
  (883, 438631, 'We have just folded space from Ix...', 'Navigator'),
  (884, 438631, 'the spice has given me accelerated evolution for four thousand years...', 'Navigator'),
  (885, 438631, 'Do not speak lightly of the spice...', 'Navigator'),
  (886, 438631, 'Geidi Prime and the Baron Harkonnen...', 'Paul'),
  (887, 438631, 'Mood''s a thing for cattle and love play...', 'Gurney'),
  (888, 438631, 'If you''d fought one whit below your abilities I''d have scratched you a good one.', 'Gurney'),
  (889, 438631, 'Is it true, that the sand can blow at seven hundred kilometers per hour?', 'Paul'),
  (890, 438631, 'some of them in the cities and they have blue- within-blue eyes...', 'Yueh'),
  (891, 438631, 'But if it is a trap then why are we going?', 'Paul'),
  (892, 438631, 'Thank you for joining me, Paul.', 'Duke Leto'),
  (893, 438631, 'they jar something deep inside, allowing him to grow.', 'Duke Leto'),
  (894, 438631, 'We''ll salvage what we can...', 'Reverend Mother'),
  (895, 438631, 'You thought only of a Duke''s desire for a son?...', 'Reverend Mother'),
  (896, 438631, 'listen to the Reverend Mother and do what she tells you.', 'Jessica'),
  (897, 438631, 'Your awareness may be powerful enough to control your instincts.', 'Reverend Mother'),
  (898, 438631, 'I will permit it to pass over me and through me.', 'Paul'),
  (899, 438631, 'A human can resist any pain.', 'Reverend Mother'),
  (900, 438631, 'Do you know of the Water of Life?...', 'Reverend Mother'),
  (901, 438631, 'It is by the juice of Sapho that thoughts acquire speed - The lips acquire stains - The stains become a warning - It is by will alone I set my mind in motion.', 'Piter'),
  (902, 438631, 'The plan to crush the Atreides.', 'Piter'),
  (903, 438631, 'and what Piter didn''t tell you is we have control of someone who is very close to Duke Leto.', 'Baron'),
  (904, 438631, 'Feyd and Rabban watch nervously.', 'Baron'),
  (905, 438631, 'I think it will go up now.', 'Atreides Radio Man'),
  (906, 438631, 'Have you noticed the line of palms along the wall...', 'Dr. Yueh'),
  (907, 438631, 'I''m sorry I''m unable to talk about it.', 'Dr. Yueh'),
  (908, 438631, 'I am the Shadout Mapes...', 'Shadout Mapes'),
  (909, 438631, 'The Palace is now secure.', 'Thufir'),
  (910, 438631, 'We must crush the Harkonnen machine on Arrakis....', 'Duke Leto'),
  (911, 438631, 'We will not be prisoners here in this place.', 'Duke Leto'),
  (912, 438631, 'The Missionaria Protectiva has been here planting protective legends against a day of Bene Gesserit need.', 'Jessica'),
  (913, 438631, 'Here is why this Fremen has taken service with me, to ask that one question.', 'Jessica'),
  (914, 438631, 'You may call him "The Duke," "My lord," or "Sire." And there is a more ancient term you might keep in mind -- "Noble Born.', 'Gurney'),
  (915, 438631, 'I hope they fit well, my lord.', 'Kynes'),
  (916, 438631, 'Perspiration passes through the first layer and is gathered in the second.', 'Kynes'),
  (917, 438631, 'Who told you how to do that?', 'Kynes'),
  (918, 438631, 'they defend the spice sands.', 'Kynes'),
  (919, 438631, 'Looks like a good patch of spice.', 'Kynes'),
  (920, 438631, 'Who is on that unlisted flight?', 'Voice'),
  (921, 438631, 'Spotter control -- give me a report by the numbers.', 'Voice'),
  (922, 438631, 'Bless the Maker and his water...', 'Kynes'),
  (923, 438631, 'What have you discovered about the Fremen, Duncan -- tell me.', 'Duke Leto'),
  (924, 438631, 'My lord, I suspect an incredible secret has been kept on this planet...', 'Duncan'),
  (925, 438631, 'You will be tied and drugged but you can still attack.', 'Yueh'),
  (926, 438631, 'We can''t let ourselves be swayed by your witch''s Voice, now, can we?', 'Baron'),
  (927, 438631, 'I''d thought of many pleasures with you.', 'Piter'),
  (928, 438631, 'Take him to his desert to die.', 'Rabban'),
  (929, 438631, 'he was brought to us as is, Baron.', 'Piter'),
  (930, 438631, 'Hurry -- This crashing may bring a worm.', 'Paul'),
  (931, 438631, 'You knew the spice would change me.', 'Paul'),
  (932, 438631, 'now I have become a killer and I will continue to kill until I have avenged your death.', 'Paul'),
  (933, 438631, 'they''ll cheer you as a rescuer...', 'Baron'),
  (934, 438631, 'Suddenly, Jessica SEES a burst of LIGHTNING illuminate the mountain of rock in the distant and the vast dunes before them.', 'Paul'),
  (935, 438631, 'I will take the boy-man...', 'Stilgar'),
  (936, 438631, 'As a leader of my people I give you my bond: teach us this weirding way and you both shall have sanctuary.', 'Stilgar'),
  (937, 438631, 'This is your secret name in our troop.', 'Stilgar'),
  (938, 438631, 'We have thousands of such caches.', 'Stilgar'),
  (939, 438631, 'No one ever dreamed there would be so many.', 'Paul'),
  (940, 438631, 'With my mother''s help, my father isolated an element of the weirding way and externalised it.', 'Paul'),
  (941, 438631, 'Death may be the result....', 'Stilgar'),
  (942, 438631, 'the blue must be made clean.', 'Jessica'),
  (943, 438631, 'I''ve always loved you....', 'Paul'),
  (944, 438631, 'it must be done each day....', 'Baron'),
  (945, 438631, 'My own name is a killing word.', 'Paul'),
  (946, 438631, 'He''s been repeating that name ever since we found him.', 'A Harkonnen Soldier'),
  (947, 438631, 'Do not get too close as he approaches...', 'Stilgar'),
  (948, 438631, 'We can''t hide it all, tell them we''ve lost only two hundred harvesters...', 'Rabban'),
  (949, 438631, 'we have just received a coded threat from the Guild.', 'Voice'),
  (950, 438631, 'It is the strangeness of your daughter.', 'Harah'),
  (951, 438631, '-- Page Missing -- In the hollow of a huge dune, Paul stops with Chani.', 'Chani'),
  (952, 438631, 'let Shai-Hulud judge now.', 'Chani'),
  (953, 438631, 'We have wormsign, the likes of which even God has never seen.', 'Stilgar'),
  (954, 438631, 'I am the messenger from Muad''dib.', 'Alia'),
  (955, 438631, 'give this little abomination to the storm.', 'Emperor'),
  (956, 438631, 'You have some idea of what I would do but I will tell it to one who has never been seen...', 'Paul'),
  (957, 438631, 'You''ll find me there staring back at you!!', 'Paul'),
  (958, 438631, 'There is a Harkonnen among you.', 'Paul'),
  (959, 438631, 'Irulan shall be my wife, opening the way for an Atreides to take the throne.', 'Paul'),
  (960, 438631, 'They will have their Holy War to cleanse the Universe...', 'Paul');
